HEADWORD: Zymoscope
<hw>Zy"mo*scope</hw> <pr>(z⟦imac⟧m"⟦osl⟧*sk⟦omac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Zyme</ets> + <ets>-scope</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.
Chem.)</fld> <def>An apparatus for determining the fermenting power of
yeast by measuring the amount of carbonic acid evolved from a given
quantity of sugar.</def></p>

